english:
  title: On the Twenty-Fifth Day, Traveling from Xiangshui Station to Yunxi Temple
  author: Lee Sim-won
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The tree shadows dance between light and dark upon the scattered stones,
    A winding path curves through and pierces the ravine's embrace.
    Wave after wave, the hidden fragrance drifts through to greet my nose—
    And so I know: deep in that distant grove, the last blossoms still linger.
  footnotes:
    - The 'hidden fragrance' (暗香) refers to the subtle scent of fading flowers, a classical image suggesting both beauty and impermanence.
    - This poem was written during a journey, likely as an observational meditation on passing beauty encountered along the way.
